.Os XINU V7
.Dd \*[release-date] 
.Dt CLOSE \&2 \*[xinu-platform]
.Sh NAME
.Nm close
.Nd device independent close routine
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Ft int Fn close "int dev"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm Close
will disconnect I/O from the device given by
.Ar dev.
It returns SYSERR if
.Ar dev
is incorrect, or is not opened for I/O.
Otherwise,
.Nm close
returns OK.
.Pp
Normally tty devices like the console do not have to be opened and
closed.
